  "text": "## Interest Rates & Earnings  \n**Q: What interest rate do I earn?**\nA: It depends on your balance:\n- £0–£10,000: 4.50% AER\n- £10,001–£50,000: 4.70% AER\n- £50,001+: 4.80% AER  \n**Q: Is the interest rate fixed or variable?**\nA: Variable. The rate changes monthly based on the Bank of England base rate. If the BoE raises rates, your rate rises. If BoE cuts rates, your rate falls.  \n**Q: How is interest calculated and paid?**\nA:\n- **Calculation:** Daily (interest accrues every day)\n- **Payment:** Monthly (paid on the last business day of the month)\n- Example: £10,000 at 4.50% earns about £37.50 per month  \n**Q: Can my interest rate decrease?**\nA: Yes. If the Bank of England cuts its base rate, your rate will decrease (but our margin of 2.5% remains constant).  \n**Q: When will my rate next change?**\nA: Rates are reviewed monthly (typically mid-month). If there's a change, it becomes effective on the 1st of the following month. We'll email you if your rate changes.  \n**Q: What if I don't like the new interest rate?**\nA: You can:\n- Keep your account (accept new rate)\n- Switch to SmartSaver Plus (if balance >£50k)\n- Close your account (no penalties)\n- Switch to a current account or other product  \n---",
